 its resolved POM only requires circe-core_3, scala3-library_3, and transitive cats/circe-numbers dependencies, and meaningful coverage is reachable by deriving Encoder/Decoder/Codec instances and exercising them with io.circe.Json/asJson without Docker, environment variables, system properties, or extra Maven dependencies.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The reported failure is an API/test-source compatibility issue: the existing 0.14.12 test calls Json.asAccumulating, which is not available on io.circe.Json in 0.15.0-M1. Generated tests should avoid relying on that removed/changed call or use the current Circe decoding API.\",\n    \"circe-parser is commonly used when parsing raw JSON strings, but it is a separate optional module and is not required to exercise circe-generic derivation; only add it if tests intentionally cover string parsing rather than the circe-generic artifact itself.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c69049e34e0db85016a2a8a20b09081969771447006add6b4\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 701, "output": 772, "cacheRead": 19968, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21441, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781172751540, "responseId": "resp_0c69049e34e0db85016a2a8a1022d08196b4aa771e6b212257"}, "toolResults": []}
